NVDAAL Test Kernel Module
=========================

Read-only kernel module that probes NVIDIA RTX 4090 (AD102) GPU registers
via BAR0 MMIO.  Does NOT claim the PCI device, so it is safe to load while
the nvidia proprietary driver is active.

Registers read:
  - PMC_BOOT_0 / BOOT_42  (chip identification)
  - GSP RISC-V CPUCTL, BCR_CTRL, mailboxes (GSP firmware state)
  - SEC2 Falcon / RISC-V status
  - WPR2 address range (write-protected region for GSP boot)
  - FWSEC-FRTS / FWSEC-SB error status
  - PTIMER (GPU timer)
  - GSP command/message queue head/tail pointers

Build
-----
  make

Load (requires root, nvidia driver must be loaded)
----
  sudo insmod nvdaal_test.ko
  # or with custom PCI address:
  sudo insmod nvdaal_test.ko pci_addr="0000:03:00.0"

View output
-----------
  dmesg | grep nvdaal_test

Unload
------
  sudo rmmod nvdaal_test

Clean
-----
  make clean

Parameters
----------
  pci_addr  - PCI address of the GPU (default: "0000:02:00.0")

Requirements
------------
  - Linux kernel headers for the running kernel
  - Root privileges to load/unload
  - NVIDIA GPU present at the specified PCI address
